definitions.definition: ( uncountable , archaic ) Hearsay , rumour ; talk ; ( countable ) an instance of this.
( countable , obsolete ) A clamour , an outcry ; a noise .

main_definition: ( uncountable , archaic ) Hearsay , rumour ; talk ; ( countable ) an instance of this.
secondary_definitions: ( countable , obsolete ) A clamour , an outcry ; a noise .

definitions.definition: An abnormal sound in the body heard on auscultation (for example, through using a stethoscope ); a murmur .

main_definition: ( medicine ) An abnormal sound in the body heard on auscultation (for example, through using a stethoscope ); a murmur . [from 19th c.]
